message.content: 'Oenothera suffrutescens' is a species of flowering plant belonging to the family Onagraceae. It is commonly known as the Texas sundrops or Mexican primrose. The plant has a shrubby growth habit and can reach a height of up to 60cm. It is characterized by its bright yellow flowers which bloom during the summer months. The flowers have four petals and are cup-shaped, opening during the day and closing at night. The leaves of 'Oenothera suffrutescens' are lance-shaped and are gray-green in color. The plant is native to the southern United States and Mexico and is commonly found in dry, rocky habitats such as prairies and open woodlands.
